OR}} '''[[Bente Skari|Bente Martinsen]]''' || align=right|525\n|- \n| align=center|2 || {{flagicon|RUS}} [[Larisa Lazutina]] || align=right|480\n|- \n| align=center|3 || {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Stefania Belmondo]] || align=right|355\n|- \n| align=center|4 || {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Anita Moen]] || align=right|336\n|-  \n| align=center|5 || {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Marit Mikkelsplass]] || align=right|281\n|- \n| align=center|6 || {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Trude Dybendahl]] || align=right|244\n|- \n| align=center|7 || {{flagicon|UKR}} [[Iryna Taranenko-Terelia]] || align=right|206\n|-\n| align=center|8 || {{flagicon|RUS}} [[Nina Gavrylyuk]] || align=right|204\n|-\n| align=center|9 || {{flagicon|CZE}} [[Kate\u0159ina Neumannov\u00e1]] || align=right|200\n|-       \n| align=center|10 || {{flagicon|RUS}} [[Olga Danilova]] || align=right|199\n|}\n{{col-break|width=1%}}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Achievements==\n;Victories in this World Cup (all-time number of victories as of 1997/98 season in parentheses)\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n;Men\n* {{flagathlete|[[Bj\u00f8rn D\u00e6hlie]]|NOR}}, 4 (41) first places\n* {{flagathlete|[[Thomas Alsgaard]]|NOR}}, 3 (4) first places\n* {{flagathlete|[[Vladimir Smirnov (skier)|Vladimir Smirnov]]|KAZ}}, 1 (30) first place\n* {{flagathlete|[[Mika Myllyl\u00e4]]|FIN}}, 1 (4) first place\n* {{flagathlete|[[Ari Palolahti]]|FIN}}, 1 (1) first place\n* {{flagathlete|[[Fulvio Valbusa]]|ITA}}, 1 (1) first place\n* {{flagathlete|[[Alexey Prokurorov]]|RUS}}, 1 (9) first place\n\n{{col-2}}\n;Women\n* {{flagathlete|[[Larisa Lazutina]]|RUS}}, 4 (12) first places\n* {{flagathlete|[[Bente Skari|Bente Martinsen]]|NOR}}, 3 (3) first places\n* {{flagathlete|[[Stefania Belmondo]]|ITA}}, 2 (17) first places\n* {{flagathlete|[[Yelena Vyalbe]]|RUS}}, 1 (45) first place\n* {{flagathlete|[[Marit Mikkelsplass]]|NOR}}, 1 (2) first place\n* {{flagathlete|[[Yuliya Chepalova]]|RUS}}, 1 (1) first place\n\n{{col-end}}\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n{{FIS Cross-Country World Cup seasons}}\n{{Wintersport season 1997\u201398}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:1997-98 FIS Cross-Country World Cup}}\n[[Category:FIS Cross-Country World Cup seasons]]\n[[Category:1997 in cross-country skiing|World Cup 1997-98]]\n[[Category:1998 in cross-country skiing|World Cup 1997-98]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Double Wintersport World Cup\n| title=1997\u201398 FIS Cross-Country World Cup\n| competition1= Overall\n| competition1men={{flagicon|NOR}} [[Thomas Alsgaard]]\n| competition1ladies={{flagicon|RUS}} [[Larisa Lazutina]] <small>(2nd title)</small>\n| competition2= Long Distance\n| competition2men={{flagicon|NOR}} [[Thomas Alsgaard]]\n| competition2ladies={{flagicon|RUS}} [[Larisa Lazutina]]\n| competition3= Sprint\n| competition3men={{flagicon|NOR}} [[Thomas Alsgaard]]\n| competition3ladies={{flagicon|NOR}} [[Bente Skari|Bente Martinsen]]\n| competition4=Nations Cup\n| competition4men={{flagicon|NOR}} [[Norway]]\n| competition4ladies={{flagicon|RUS}} [[Russia]]\n| mixedcompetition1=Nations Cup Overall\n| mixedcompetition1both={{flagicon|NOR}} [[Norway]]\n| menlocations= 9 venues\n| ladieslocations= 9 venues\n| menindividual= 12 events\n| ladiesindividual= 12 events\n| relaymen= 4 events\n| relayladies= 4 events\n| previous=[[1996\u201397 FIS Cross-Country World Cup|1996\u201397]]\n| next=[[1998\u201399 FIS Cross-Country World Cup|1998\u201399]]\n}}\n\nThe '''1997\u201398 FIS Cross-Country World Cup'''  was the 17th official [[FIS Cross-Country World Cup|World Cup]] season in [[cross-country skiing (sport)|cross-country skiing]] for men and ladies. The season began in [[Beitost\u00f8len]], [[Norway]], on 22 November 1997 and finished at [[Holmenkollen]], [[Oslo]], [[Norway]], on 14 March 1998. [[Thomas Alsgaard]] of [[Norway]] won the overall men's cup,<ref>{{cite web|title=CUP STANDING CROSS-COUNTRY WORLD CUP 1998 MEN|url=https://data.fis-ski.com/cross-country/cup-standings.html?suchen=true&export_standing=&suchcompetitorid=&suchseason=1998&suchgender=M&suchnation=&sector=CC&suchcup=WC&discipline=ALL&search=Search|publisher=[[International Ski Federation]]|accessdate=20 March 2018}}</ref> and [[Larisa Lazutina]] of [[Russia]] won the women's.<ref>{{cite web|title=CUP STANDING CROSS-COUNTRY WORLD CUP 1998 LADIES|url=https://data.fis-ski.com/cross-country/cup-standings.html?suchen=true&export_standing=&suchcompetitorid=&suchseason=1998&suchgender=L&suchnation=&sector=CC&suchcup=WC&discipline=ALL&search=Search|publisher=[[International Ski Federation]]|accessdate=20 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Calendar==\n=== Men ===\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" cellpadding=\"3\" cellspacing=\"0\" border=\"1\" style=\"background:#fff; font-size:86%; line-height:16px; border:grey solid 1px; border-collapse:collapse;\"\n|+ C \u2013 Classic / F \u2013 Freestyle\n!scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#ccc; width=20 px;\"|{{Abbr|WC|World Cup}}\n!scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#ccc; width:120px;\"|Date\n!scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#ccc; width:160px;\"|Place\n!scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#ccc; width:130px;\"|Discipline\n!scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#ccc; width:185px;\"|Winner\n!scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#ccc; width:185px;\"|Second\n!scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#ccc; width:185px;\"|Third\n!scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#ccc; width:10px;\" |{{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}} \n|-\n| align=center|1\n| align=right|22 November 1997 &nbsp;\n| {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Beitost\u00f8len]]\n| align=right|10 km C &nbsp;\n| {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Bj\u00f8rn D\u00e6hlie]]\n| {{flagicon|KAZ}} [[Vladimir Smirnov (skier)|Vladimir Smirnov]]\n| {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Erling Jevne]]\n| <ref>{{cite web|title=Men's 10 km C \u2013 Beitost\u00f8len|url=https://data.fis-ski.com/dynamic/results.html?sector=CC&raceid=1164|publisher=[[International Ski Federation]]}}</ref>\n|-\n| align=center|2\n| align=right|10 December 1997 &nbsp;\n| {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Milano]]\n| align=right|Sprint F &nbsp; \n| {{flagicon|FIN}} [[Ari Palolahti]]\n| {{flagicon|SWE}} [[Thobias Fredriksson]]\n| {{flagicon|AUT}